se-castrense/paganese-calcio-1926/3109144/ Report]\n|goals1=\n* [[Mamadou Tounkara]] {{goal|37}}\n* [[Stefano Antezza|Antezza]] {{goal|84}}\n|goals2=\n* Thomas Alberti {{goal|71}}\n|stadium=[[Stadio Enrico Rocchi]]\n|location=[[Viterbo]]\n|attendance=1,200\n|referee={{flagicon|Italy}} Francesco Cosso\n}}\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=1 September 2019\n|time=17:30 [[Central European Time|CET]]\n|round=Match 2\n|team1=[[S.S.C. Bari|Bari]]\n|score=1 - 3 \n|team2=[[A.S. Viterbese Castrense|Viterbese Castrense]]\n|result=W\n|report=[https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/01/italy/serie-c1/as-bari/viterbese-castrense/3109145/ Report]\n|goals1=\n* [[Simone Simeri|Simeri]] {{yel}}\n* [[Mirco Antenucci|Antenucci]] {{goal|67|pen.}}\n|goals2=\n* [[Mamadou Tounkara]] {{yel}} {{goal|31}} {{goal|90+1}}\n* [[Stefano Antezza|Antezza]] {{yel}}\n* Andrea Errico {{yel}}\n* [[Daniel Bezziccheri|Bezziccheri]] {{goal|76}}\n|stadium=[[Stadio San Nicola]]\n|location=[[Bari]]\n|attendance=12,066\n|referee={{flagicon|Italy}} Matteo Marcenaro\n}}\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=8 September 2019\n|time=17:30 [[Central European Time|CET]]\n|round=Match 3\n|team1=[[A.S. Viterbese Castrense|Viterbese Castrense]]\n|score=1 - 2\n|team2=[[AZ Picerno|Picerno]]\n|result=L\n|report=[https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/08/italy/serie-c1/viterbese-castrense/picerno/3109164/ Report]\n|goals1=\n* [[Federico Baschirotto|Baschirotto]] {{sentoff|2|35|70}}\n* Zhivko Atanasov {{yel}}\n* [[Stefano Antezza|Antezza]] {{yel}}\n* [[Mamadou Tounkara]] {{yel}} {{goal|57}}\n|goals2=\n* Nebil Caidi {{goal|25}}\n* Emanuele Santaniello {{goal|31}}\n* Mario Vrdoljak {{yel}}\n* [[Claudio Sparacello|Sparcello]] {{yel}}\n* Antonio Calabrese {{yel}}\n|stadium=[[Stadio Enrico Rocchi]]\n|location=[[Viterbo]]\n|attendance=1,300\n|referee={{flagicon|Italy}} Emanuele Frascaro\n}}\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=15 September 2019\n|time=15:00 [[Central European Time|CET]]\n|round=Match 4\n|team1=[[Calcio Catania|Catania]]\n|score=1 - 0\n|team2=[[A.S. Viterbese Castrense|Viterbese Castrense]]\n|result=L\n|report=[https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/15/italy/serie-c1/calcio-catania/viterbese-castrense/3109168/ Report]\n|goals1=\n* [[Emmanuel Mbende|Mbende]] {{yel}}\n* [[Nana Welbeck|Welbeck]] {{yel}}\n* Francesco Lodi {{goal|50|pen.}}\n* [[Davide Di Molfetta|Di Molfetta]] {{yel}}\n* [[Jacopo Dall'Oglio|Dall'Oglio]] {{yel}}\n|goals2=\n* Zhivko Atansov {{yel}}\n* [[Daniel Bezziccheri|Bezziccheri]] {{yel}}\n|stadium=[[Stadio Angelo Massimino]]\n|location=[[Catania]]\n|attendance=7,669\n|referee={{flagicon|Italy}} Mario Vigile\n}}\n\n====Coppa Italia====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=4 August 2019\n|time=18:00\n|round=First Round\n|team1=[[Piacenza Calcio 1919|Piacenza]]\n|score=1 - 1\n|aet=yes\n|penaltyscore=3 \u2013 2\n|team2=[[A.S. Viterbese Castrense|Viterbese Castrense]]\n|result=L\n|report=[https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/04/italy/coppa-italia/piacenza-calcio/viterbese-castrense/3099896/ Report]\n|goals1=\n* Youssouph Sylla {{goal|97}}\n* [[Thomas Bolis|Bolis]] {{yel|100}}\n|goals2=\n* Sebastiano Svidercoshi {{goal|94}}\n* Jari Vandeputte {{yel|105+2}}\n|stadium=[[Stadio Leonardo Garilli]]\n|location=[[Piacenza]]\n|attendance=759\n|referee={{flagicon|Italy}} Enrico Maggio\n}}\n\n====Coppa Italia Serie C====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date=6 November 2019\n|time=18:30 \n|round=Second Round\n|team1=[[A.S. Viterbese Castrense|Viterbese Castrense]]\n|score=0 - 1\n|team2=[[S.S. Teramo Calcio|Teramo]]\n|result=L\n|report=[https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/11/06/italy/coppa-italia-serie-c/viterbese-castrense/teramo-calcio/3164801/ Report]\n|goals1=\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[Stadio Enrico Rocchi]]\n|location=[[Viterbo]]\n|attendance=\n|referee=\n}}\n\n==References==\n1. *https://uk.soccerway.com/teams/italy/viterbese-castrense/34511/*\n2. *https://www.betexplorer.com/soccer/team/viterbese/n7aJv4Cr/*\n==External links==\n*{{in lang|it}} [http://viterbesecastrense.it/ Official homepage]\n\n{{Serie C}}\n{{Football in Italy}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Viterbese}}\n[[Category:Football clubs in Italy]]\n[[Category:Viterbo]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1909]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Lazio]]\n[[Category:Serie C clubs]]\n[[Category:1909 establishments in Italy]]\n\n\n{{Italy-footyclub-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Woodlot", "label": "safe", "comment": "spelling", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019%E2%80%9320_A.S._Viterbese_Castrense_season"}
{"title_page": "DiaSorin", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = DiaSorin\n| logo                = DiaSorin-logo.svg\n| caption             = \n| type                = [[Societ\u00e0 per azioni]]\n| traded_as           = {{ISE|IT0003492391|DIA}}\n| fate                = \n| predecessor         = \n| successor           = \n| foundation          = {{Start date|2000}}\n| founder             = \n| defunct             = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location_city       = [[Saluggia]]\n| location_country    = Italy\n| locations           = \n| area_served         = \n| key_people          = [[Gustavo Denegri]] <small>([[Chairman]])</small><br>Carlo Rosa <small>([[chief executive officer|CEO]])</small>\n| industry            = [[Biotechnology]]\n| products            = [[In vitro diagnostics]] instruments and services\n| services            = \n| revenue             = {{increase}}[[Euro|\u20ac]]669 million<ref name=fy2018 />\n| revenue_year        = 2018\n| operating_income    = \n| net_income          = \n| assets              = \n| equity              = \n| owner               = \n| num_employees       = 1,971 (2018)<ref name=fy2018 />\n| parent              = \n| divisions           = \n| subsid              = \n| homepage            = {{URL| https://diasoringroup.com}}\n| footnotes           = \n| intl                = \n| Slogan              = Diagnostics is for Life\n}}\n\n'''DiaSorin''' is an Italian multinational [[biotechnology]] company that produces and markets [[in vitro diagnostics]] [[reagent]] kits used in [[immunodiagnostics]] and [[molecular diagnostics]]. The group was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in [[Saluggia]], Italy. \nThe production platform of the Group is now divided into several plants located in Europe, the United States and Africa: [[Saluggia]] and [[Gerenzano]] (Italy), [[Dietzenbach]] (Germany), [[Stillwater, Minnesota]] (US), [[Dartford]] (UK).\nThe company is a constituent of the [[FTSE Italia Mid Cap]] index.\n\n== Activities ==\nDiaSorin focuses its efforts to 8 fields of immunodiagnostics: Infectious diseases, Bone and Mineral, Endocrinology, Hypertension, Oncology, Gastro-Intestinal infections, Autoimmunity and Brain and Cardiac markers.\n\nThe company is also active in molecular diagnostics for infectious diseases and for the detection of some forms of leukemia.<ref name=\"fy2017\">{{cite web | url=http://www.diasorin.com/en/investor-relations/total-shareholders-basis |title=Annual Financial Report at December 31, 2017 | accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nDiaSorin develops, manufactures and markets tests for the diagnosis of infectious diseases or hormonal disorders. The diagnostic tests are aimed at both private and hospital analysis laboratories worldwide, in immunodiagnostics and molecular diagnostics markets.\n\nIn immunodiagnostics, DiaSorin offers the market proprietary-based platforms on the CLIA ([[Chemiluminescence]]) and ELISA ([[Colorimetry]]) technologies.\n\nIn molecular diagnostics, DiaSorin offers the market diversified proprietary platforms based on the 3 phases of the detection process: extraction, amplification and diagnosis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diasorin.com/sites/default/files/docs/diasorin_s.p.a.-annual_financial_report_2017_0.pdf|title=DiaSorin - Annual Financial Report 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe origins of the company date back to 1968, when near [[Vercelli]] on an initiative of [[Fiat S.p.A.|Fiat]] and Montecatini, the \"Sorin Biomedica\" was founded by the \"Societ\u00e0 Ricerche Impianti Nucleari - Sorin\".<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.diasorin.com/en/company/our-history|title=DiaSorin - Our History|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 1997 the Company acquired control of American Incstar Inc., and part of its operations were later sold to American Standard Inc.<ref name=\":0\" /> DiaSorin was founded in 2000, through a management buyout operation led by the Italians Carlo Rosa and Gustavo Denegri.<ref name = dia>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/economia/affari-e-finanza/2018/04/16/news/diasorin_via_da_dublino_grazie_al_patent_box_ma_ora_maggiori_certezze-193999139/|title=DiaSorin: \"Via da Dublino grazie al patent box. Ma ora maggiori certezze\"|date=16 April 2018|access-date=17 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002 DiaSorin acquired BYC Sangtec and the rights to the LIAISON platform. The commercial expansion led to the opening of new branches in [[Mexico]], [[Israel]], and [[China]]. The LIAISON portfolio was enriched with products for new and clinical specialty areas. In the same year the Group started the conversion of the tests previously developed with ELISA technology on the most recent and automated CLIA.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn July 19, 2007 the DiaSorin title debuted at [[Borsa Italiana]] Stock Exchange.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.borsaitaliana.it/borsa/azioni/scheda/IT0003492391.html?lang=en|title=Borsa Italiana - DiaSorin|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014 the company obtained the approval of [[Hepatitis]], [[Retrovirus]] tests in China; in the same year, DiaSorin launched new tests to detect [[leukemia]]s. DiaSorin Group signed an agreement in 2015 with [[Beckman Coulter]] for the commercialization in China of DiaSorin Hepatitis and [[HIV]] tests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beckmancoulter.com/it/about-beckman-coulter/newsroom/press-releases/2016/diasorin-and-beckman-coulter-form-strategic-partnership|title=DiaSorin and Beckman Coulter Form Strategic Partnership to Bring the Liaison XL Hepatitis and HIV Products to the U.S. Market|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, the group acquired of Focus Diagnostics\u2019 business unit, enabling the Group to expand its activities in molecular diagnostics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.genengnews.com/gen-news-highlights/diasorin-to-acquire-quest-s-focus-diagnostics-for-300m/81252541/|title=DiaSorin to Acquire Quest's Focus Diagnostics for $300M|work=GEN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.focusdx.com/news/diasorin-acquires-focus-diagnostics-molecular-and-immunoassay-product-business|title=DiaSorin Completes {{sic|Acqui|stion|nolink=yes|expected=Acquisition}} of the Focus Diagnostics' Molecular and Immunoassay Product Business from Quest Diagnostics|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, a partnership with [[Qiagen]] offered an automated solution for detection of [[tuberculosis]] with QuantiFERON-TB Gold Plus available on the LIAISON analyzers. That was also the year of the [[Siemens Healthineers]] ELISA business acquisition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diasorin.com/en/press-releases/diasorin-acquire-elisa-immunodiagnostic-business-portfolio-and-associated-assets|title=DiaSorin to acquire ELISA immunodiagnostic business portfolio and associated assets from SIEMENS HEALTHINEERS|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018 the [[Saluggia]] branch began a partnership with Meridian for the distribution of a ''[[Helicobacter pylori]]'' detection test in the United States and United Kingdom. The companies have put in place a framenwork under which they may work together on the development of new tests and products.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2018/10/09/1618864/0/en/DiaSorin-and-Meridian-Enter-Into-a-Strategic-Collaboration-to-Sell-Helicobacter-Pylori-Stool-Antigen-Test-in-the-United-States-and-in-the-United-Kingdom.html|title=DiaSorin and Meridian Enter Into a Strategic Collaboration to Sell Helicobacter Pylori Stool Antigen Test in the United States and in the United Kingdom|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n2020: In February and March, from the novel coronavirus outbreak, DiaSorin has promptly devised and developed a [https://diasoringroup.com/en/media/covid-19-updates rapid and accurate molecular diagnostic test on our LIAISON MDX platform] intended to detect all the currently known variants of the COVID-19.\u00a0 The test enables sample-to-answer results within less than 60 minutes compared to the 5-7 hours currently necessary to report patient results.\n\nOn 7 April 2020, DiaSorin announces the development of a [https://diasoringroup.com/en/investors/financial-corner/press-releases/igg-test-detect-immune-response-sars-cov-2 new IgG CLIA test] to identify antibodies against [[SARS-CoV-2]] antibody test, receiving both the CE mark and emergency use authorisation from the [[Food and Drug Administration]].<ref>{{cite web |title=LIAISON\u00ae SARS-CoV-2 IgG |url=https://www.diasorin.com/en/news/liaisonr-sars-cov-2-igg |website=DiaSorin}}</ref>\n\n== Shareholder base ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Shareholder (2019<ref name=ataglance />)\n! Share % \n|-\n| Finde SS\n| 60.06% \n|-\n| Rosa Carlo\n| 8.451% \n|-\n| Even Chen Menachem\n| 2.805%\n|-\n| Market\n| 26.66%\n|}\n\n== Financial data ==\nDiaSorin is listed since 2007 in the Italian Stock Exchange and today in the FTSE Italy Mid Cap Index.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n \n|-\n!(in thousand Euros)<ref name=fy2017 />\n! 2007\n! 2008\n! 2009\n! 2010\n! 2011\n! 2012\n! 2013\n! 2014\n! 2015\n! 2016\n! 2017\n! 2018\n!2019\n|-\n| Sales and service revenues\n|206,3\n|244,6\n|304,1\n|404,5\n|440\n|433,7\n|434,8\n|443,7\n|449,1\n|569,3\n|637,4\n|669,2  \n|706,3\n|-\n|Cost of sales\n|(73,8)\n|(84)\n|(90,4)\n|(119,8)\n|(126,1)\n|(136,4)\n|(135,1)\n|(145) \n|(157,2)  \n|(180,1)  \n|(205,5)\n|(214,4)      \n|217,6\n|-\n|Gross profit\n|132,5\n|160,6\n|213,6\n|284,7\n|313,8\n|297,3\n|299,6\n|298,7\n|341,8\n|389,1\n|431,9\n|455,8    \n|488,7\n|-\n|EBIT\n|47,5\n|70,7\n|106,4\n|145,5\n|163,3\n|140,2\n|134,6\n|129,8\n|152\n|172,6\n|184,4\n|204,5   \n|217,9\n|-\n|Profit before taxes\n|44,1\n|59,8\n|103,7\n|144,9\n|158,2\n|137,4\n|129,3\n|128,1\n|150,1\n|168,1\n|178,7\n|204,4   \n|216,3\n|-\n|Net result\n|26,3 \n|37,4\n|70\n|90,4\n|99,6\n|87,6\n|83,1\n|84\n|100,5\n|112,6\n|139,8\n|158,1        \n|175,7\n|-\n|EBITDA\n|61,5\n|85,6\n|123,6\n|167,1\n|190\n|169,5\n|163\n|160,2\n|184,9  \n|217,3  \n|237,9\n|255,4       \n|276,8\n|}\n\n== Management ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Role\n! Name\n|-\n| Chairman\n| [[Gustavo Denegri]]\n|-\n| Chief Executive Officer\n| [[Carlo Rosa]]\n|-\n| Senior Corporate VP e Chief Financial Officer\n| Piergiorgio Pedron\n|-\n| Chief Commercial Officer\n| [[Chen Even]]\n|-\n| Senior Corporate VP Human Resources\n| [[Stefano Ronchi]] \t\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|\n<ref name=group>{{cite web | url=https://diasoringroup.com/en/group |title=Diasorin official website| accessdate=12 July 2019}}</ref>\n<ref name=about>{{cite web | url=http://www.diasorin.com/en/diagnostic-specialist |title=About us | accessdate=24 November 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=ataglance>{{cite web | url=http://www.diasorin.com/en/investor-relations/total-shareholders-basis |title=Diasorin official website, Total shareholders' basis | accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Borsa Italiana]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Piedmont]]\n[[Category:Biotechnology companies established in 2000]]\n[[Category:Biotechnology companies of Italy]]\n[[Category:Italian brands]]\n[[Category:2000 establishments in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = DiaSorin\n| logo = DiaSorin-logo.svg \n| caption = \n| type = [[Societ\u00e0 per azioni]]\n| traded_as = {{ISE|IT0003492391|DIA}}\n| fate = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| foundation = {{Start date|2000}}\n| founder = \n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location_city = [[Saluggia]]\n| location_country = Italy\n| locations = \n| area_served = \n| key_people = [[Gustavo Denegri]] <small>([[Chairman]])</small><br>Carlo Rosa <small>([[chief executive officer|CEO]])</small>\n| industry = [[Biotechnology]]\n| products = [[In vitro diagnostics]] instruments and services\n| services = \n| revenue = {{increase}}[[Euro|\u20ac]]669 million<ref name=fy2018 />\n| revenue_year = 2018\n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = 1,971 (2018)<ref name=fy2018 />\n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{URL| https://diasoringroup.com}}\n| footnotes = \n| intl = \n}}\n\n'''DiaSorin''' is an Italian multinational [[biotechnology]] company that produces and markets [[in vitro diagnostics]] [[reagent]] kits used in [[immunodiagnostics]] and [[molecular diagnostics]]. The group was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in [[Saluggia]], Italy. \nThe production platform of the Group is now divided into several plants located in Europe, the United States and Africa: [[Saluggia]] and [[Gerenzano]] (Italy), [[Dietzenbach]] (Germany), [[Stillwater, Minnesota]] (US), [[Dartford]] (UK).\nThe company is a constituent of the [[FTSE Italia Mid Cap]] index.\n\n== Activities ==\nDiaSorin focuses its efforts to 8 fields of immunodiagnostics: Infectious diseases, Bone and Mineral, Endocrinology, Hypertension, Oncology, Gastro-Intestinal infections, Autoimmunity and Brain and Cardiac markers.\n\nThe company is also active in molecular diagnostics for infectious diseases and for the detection of some forms of leukemia.<ref name=\"fy2017\">{{cite web | url=http://www.diasorin.com/en/investor-relations/total-shareholders-basis |title=Annual Financial Report at December 31, 2017 | accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nDiaSorin develops, manufactures and markets tests for the diagnosis of infectious diseases or hormonal disorders. The diagnostic tests are aimed at both private and hospital analysis laboratories worldwide, in immunodiagnostics and molecular diagnostics markets.\n\nIn immunodiagnostics, DiaSorin offers the market proprietary-based platforms on the CLIA ([[Chemiluminescence]]) and ELISA ([[Colorimetry]]) technologies.\n\nIn molecular diagnostics, DiaSorin offers the market diversified proprietary platforms based on the 3 phases of the detection process: extraction, amplification and diagnosis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diasorin.com/sites/default/files/docs/diasorin_s.p.a.-annual_financial_report_2017_0.pdf|title=DiaSorin - Annual Financial Report 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe origins of the company date back to 1968, when near [[Vercelli]] on an initiative of [[Fiat S.p.A.|Fiat]] and Montecatini, the \"Sorin Biomedica\" was founded by the \"Societ\u00e0 Ricerche Impianti Nucleari - Sorin\".<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.diasorin.com/en/company/our-history|title=DiaSorin - Our History|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In 1997 the Company acquired control of American Incstar Inc., and part of its operations were later sold to American Standard Inc.<ref name=\":0\" /> DiaSorin was founded in 2000, through a management buyout operation led by the Italians Carlo Rosa and Gustavo Denegri.<ref name = dia>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/economia/affari-e-finanza/2018/04/16/news/diasorin_via_da_dublino_grazie_al_patent_box_ma_ora_maggiori_certezze-193999139/|title=DiaSorin: \"Via da Dublino grazie al patent box. Ma ora maggiori certezze\"|date=16 April 2018|access-date=17 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002 DiaSorin acquired BYC Sangtec and the rights to the LIAISON platform. The commercial expansion led to the opening of new branches in [[Mexico]], [[Israel]], and [[China]]. The LIAISON portfolio was enriched with products for new and clinical specialty areas. In the same year the Group started the conversion of the tests previously developed with ELISA technology on the most recent and automated CLIA.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn July 19, 2007 the DiaSorin title debuted at [[Borsa Italiana]] Stock Exchange.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.borsaitaliana.it/borsa/azioni/scheda/IT0003492391.html?lang=en|title=Borsa Italiana - DiaSorin|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014 the company obtained the approval of [[Hepatitis]], [[Retrovirus]] tests in China; in the same year, DiaSorin launched new tests to detect [[leukemia]]s. DiaSorin Group signed an agreement in 2015 with [[Beckman Coulter]] for the commercialization in China of DiaSorin Hepatitis and [[HIV]] tests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beckmancoulter.com/it/about-beckman-coulter/newsroom/press-releases/2016/diasorin-and-beckman-coulter-form-strategic-partnership|title=DiaSorin and Beckman Coulter Form Strategic Partnership to Bring the Liaison XL Hepatitis and HIV Products to the U.S. Market|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, the group acquired of Focus Diagnostics\u2019 business unit, enabling the Group to expand its activities in molecular diagnostics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.genengnews.com/gen-news-highlights/diasorin-to-acquire-quest-s-focus-diagnostics-for-300m/81252541/|title=DiaSorin to Acquire Quest's Focus Diagnostics for $300M|work=GEN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.focusdx.com/news/diasorin-acquires-focus-diagnostics-molecular-and-immunoassay-product-business|title=DiaSorin Completes {{sic|Acqui|stion|nolink=yes|expected=Acquisition}} of the Focus Diagnostics' Molecular and Immunoassay Product Business from Quest Diagnostics|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, a partnership with [[Qiagen]] offered an automated solution for detection of [[tuberculosis]] with QuantiFERON-TB Gold Plus available on the LIAISON analyzers. That was also the year of the [[Siemens Healthineers]] ELISA business acquisition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.diasorin.com/en/press-releases/diasorin-acquire-elisa-immunodiagnostic-business-portfolio-and-associated-assets|title=DiaSorin to acquire ELISA immunodiagnostic business portfolio and associated assets from SIEMENS HEALTHINEERS|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018 the [[Saluggia]] branch began a partnership with Meridian for the distribution of a ''[[Helicobacter pylori]]'' detection test in the United States and United Kingdom. The companies have put in place a framenwork under which they may work together on the development of new tests and products.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2018/10/09/1618864/0/en/DiaSorin-and-Meridian-Enter-Into-a-Strategic-Collaboration-to-Sell-Helicobacter-Pylori-Stool-Antigen-Test-in-the-United-States-and-in-the-United-Kingdom.html|title=DiaSorin and Meridian Enter Into a Strategic Collaboration to Sell Helicobacter Pylori Stool Antigen Test in the United States and in the United Kingdom|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n2020: In February and March, from the novel coronavirus outbreak, DiaSorin has promptly devised and developed a [https://diasoringroup.com/en/media/covid-19-updates rapid and accurate molecular diagnostic test on our LIAISON MDX platform] intended to detect all the currently known variants of the COVID-19.\u00a0 The test enables sample-to-answer results within less than 60 minutes compared to the 5-7 hours currently necessary to report patient results.\n\nOn 7 April 2020, DiaSorin announces the development of a [https://diasoringroup.com/en/investors/financial-corner/press-releases/igg-test-detect-immune-response-sars-cov-2 new IgG CLIA test] to identify antibodies against [[SARS-CoV-2]] antibody test, receiving both the CE mark and emergency use authorisation from the [[Food and Drug Administration]].<ref>{{cite web |title=LIAISON\u00ae SARS-CoV-2 IgG |url=https://www.diasorin.com/en/news/liaisonr-sars-cov-2-igg |website=DiaSorin}}</ref>\n\n== Shareholder base ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Shareholder (2019<ref name=ataglance />)\n! Share % \